{"name":"Amplification","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>A talent which does nothing itself, but which increases the power and effect(s) of other talents, spells or esoteric phenomena. The effect is unpredictable at best, wild at worst. Amplification does not increase the ML/TL of a phenomenon, but once the event is happening, it can be used to increase its power and effect. With the basic talent, the user is able to activate the power, which acts generally on some or all phenomena within about twenty feet. The talent does not detect events.</p>\n<p>ML66+ The user can specify a single event to amplify (touching a companion who is casting a spell, for example, will increase the power of the spell).</p>\n<p>ML76+ The user may be generally aware of &lsquo;amplifiable&rsquo; phenomena in his vicinity (within about twenty feet), but not of their nature.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES </strong>may involve dizziness, burred vision, and feelings of surplus energy.</p>\n<p>In the dormant stage, the talent may self-trigger in the presence of esoteric phenomena, causing unexpected results.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> often causes the object event to misfire, aural shock is also common for the user.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 4","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, Feniri, Angberelius","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":2,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"kEVnFFTtFhW7FHPq"}
{"name":"SPIRIT","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB3","description":"<p>Spirit is the personality equivalent of CONDITION. The ability to wage Mental Conflict, resist aural shock, etc.. This skill is &ldquo;semi-automatic&rdquo;; it is calculated and opened when the character is first exposed to Mental Conflict or aural shock.</p>\n<p>For Artificial Personalities, SB equals EGO. Mental conflict takes several forms. The basic resolution procedure is for each party to the conflict to test Spirit and compare results.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 7","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @wil, @wil","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":2,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"tHWNAkMucp2oPzro"}
{"name":"Charm","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>A talent by means of which its user attempts to influence a victim. Charm effects vary at GM discretion, but the usual effect is to freeze the victim in place for a short period of time.</p>\n<p>This talent is most common in rare creatures such as dragons and some ethereals. Creatures with Charm are indicated in the BESTIARY. In such cases a ML is provided. Range may be given in the bestiary. If no range is given, eye contact is necessary. For most purposes, the range of the effect (effective eye contact) is equal to the charmer&rsquo;s height or length.</p>\n<p>The Charmer tests CHARM and the victim test SPIRIT. The resulting success levels are cross-indexed on the Charm Matrix and the result is read.</p>\n<p>The effect of charm is usually no more than a 10 second pause, which might seem a minor effect and a minor talent, were it not for the fact that the pause usually occurs in a life-threatening situation.</p>\n<table style=\"height: 112px; width: 500px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 400px; background-color: darkred; text-align: center; font-variant: small-caps;\" colspan=\"5\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>Charm Matrix</strong></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 400px; text-align: center;\" colspan=\"5\">Charmer tests CHARM victim tests SPIRIT. <br />Cross-index the charmer's success (red) with the victim's success (green)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40px; height: 16px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; text-align: center; background-color: green;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>CF</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; text-align: center; background-color: green;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>MF</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; text-align: center; background-color: green;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>MS</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; text-align: center; background-color: green;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>CS</strong></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40px; height: 16px; text-align: center; background-color: red;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>CF</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\">Charm Misfires</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\">Charm Misfires</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-align: center;\">Charm Misfires</span></td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-align: center;\">Charm Misfires</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40px; text-align: center; background-color: red; height: 16px;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>MF</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; text-align: center; background-color: white;\">No Effect</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; text-align: center; background-color: white;\">No Effect</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; text-align: center; background-color: white;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">No Effect</span></td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"text-align: center;\">Charm Misfires</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40px; text-align: center; background-color: red; height: 16px;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>MS</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\">Frozen 1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\">Frozen 2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; text-align: center; background-color: white;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">No Effect</span></td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; text-align: center; background-color: white;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">No Effect</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 40px; text-align: center; background-color: red; height: 16px;\">\n<div style=\"color: white;\"><strong>CS</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\">Frozen 1</td>\n<td style=\"width: 90px; height: 16px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\">Frozen 1</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; background-color: lightyellow; text-align: center;\">Frozen 2</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16px; width: 90px; text-align: center; background-color: white;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">No Effect</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Frozen 1: the victim cannot move until the charmer&rsquo;s next turn.</p>\n<p>Frozen 2: As Frozen 1, but the victim is able to defend itself.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> may involve Jamais vu, Deja vu, dizziness, headaches, and burred vision.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> effects include severe incapacitating headaches, temporary true&ndash;blindness, and SHOCK. The effects tend to be relatively minor.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 56\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8.000000pt; font-family: 'KorinnaBT';\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 4","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, Tai, Nadai, Tarael","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":2,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"d2RJnoHQdEDjMQcW"}
{"name":"Clairvoyance","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to visualise events currently occurring at a remote location.</p>\n<p>Clairvoyance may be used in either of two ways:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The clairvoyant enters trance for one minute to transfer the point of perception up to ML yards away; MS enables him to watch (CS also to listen and smell); or<br /><br /></li>\n<li>The Clairvoyant enters trance for 10&ndash;60 minutes and attempts to focus on a specific remote object or person whose location may or may not be known. With MS the clairvoyant gains a vague vision of the object's current situation, activities, etc. There are no range restrictions with the second form.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Marginal Success, with either method, usually produces blurred or misted, intermittent vision. With CS, vision is clearer.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> usually involve vivid dreams of faraway people and things often accompanied by dizziness and/or headaches (these are often taken for hangovers). Blurred vision and mirage&ndash;like hallucinations are also fairly common.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> effects include severe incapacitating headaches, temporary true&ndash;blindness, etc.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 4","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, Tai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"ILl9I6C0ckkU7skx"}
{"name":"Disembodiment","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to detach the ethereal component from the corporeal component. With success, the character's spirit is detached and his body is left in a state of metabolic suspension (unconscious). See Astral (REALITY 12).</p>\n<p>✟ At ML 76+, the user is able to dematerialise its corporeal component form (leaving no vulnerable body in the material world until the spirit returns and remanifests).</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> include dreams of floating through space, various &ldquo;altered mental states&rdquo; jamais vu, light-headedness, peculiar shivers (&ldquo;someone is walking on my grave&rdquo;), dizziness and a feeling of being watched.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> effects commonly include extreme weakness and dizziness, disorientation, and loss of balance</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 5","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, hirin, nadai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"SsFZkojFEPglnemF"}
{"name":"Extratemporality","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to &ldquo;step outside of time&rdquo;. This talent is triggered by extreme stress. Its effect is that the character&rsquo;s surroundings seem to slow down. This gives the character time to think and, with CS, limited time to act. In a combat situation, CS might generate a Tactical Advantage with a 50% EML bonus. With MS, the effect might include a &ldquo;moment of clarity&rdquo;, a profound understanding to the present situation (possibly involving advice from the GM).</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> blackouts, profound quiescence, vivid dreams of past (and sometimes future) experiences (being &ldquo;unstuck in time&rdquo;); altered mental states including a feeling that one does not &ldquo;belong&rdquo;</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> effects include weakness, dizziness, extreme disorientation, temporary loss of motor function and/or cognitive facility, shock/coma.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 5","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, hirin, nadai, tai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":2,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"U8jSt8i4FWgxR01i"}
{"name":"Healing","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>This ability may be used in any of five ways. A healer cannot use his talent</p>\n<p>on himself. All five options require skin contact between the healer and patient:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>EMPATHETIC DIAGNOSIS An attempt to diagnose the patient's emotional state and/or physical well&ndash;being; acquired information depends on the level of success.<br /><br /></li>\n<li>INVIGORATION An attempt to remove fatigue; CS eliminates all FATIGUE POINTS, MS removes 50%.<br /><br /></li>\n<li>HALT BLOODLOSS An attempt to stop a single wound bleeding. CS stops bleeding completely. MS reduces bloodloss by 1 BP, eliminating B1 bleeding, or reducing B2 to B1.<br /><br /></li>\n<li>HASTEN HEALING An attempt to increase the healing rate of one identified ailment. CS increases healing rate by 2, MS by 1. If this brings healing rate to H5 (or more), any infection is defeated.<br /><br />Cannot be applied to the same injury ✟more than once; or ✟more than once per day.<br /><br /></li>\n<li>✟REVIVIFICATION An attempt to restore life to a dead patient. The healer accumulates double normal fatigue. EML is reduced by the number of hours the victim has been dead. The victim is brought back to life with any success, but remains in shock with MS. Revivification does not heal injuries; this requires further treatment. ✟Revivification can only occur with CS.</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> include emotional empathy (crying at the distress of others) and sympathy pains (someone else hurts his hand, the healer feels pain).</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> sometimes the healer acquires some or all of the patient&rsquo;s ailment(s) &mdash; thus creating two patients in place of one.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 5","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, masara, skorus","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"ERADpvu2pFEnVWul"}
{"name":"Hex","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>Sometimes called the evil eye. A successful hex halves EML the next time the victim attempts to use any skill, talent, spell, etc. If the hexer achieves CS, the situation when the hex is applied may be specified by the hexer. CF with Hex rebounds the curse on the hexer, a fact that is kept secret until it manifests with the hexer's next attempt to use a skill/etc.</p>\n<p>If the hexer has in his possession a part of the victim (nail pairings, lock of hair etc.) increase EML by 20. Such items may be used only once. The talent takes 15&ndash;SI minutes to use.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> usually include the character and/or the character&rsquo;s companions having unusually spells of good (or more likely bad) luck.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> usually results in rebound. In extreme cases, the character may experience a long run of bad luck without necessarily realising it.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 5","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, ahnu","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"OYsxoVKwQM23pJtA"}
{"name":"Medium","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>A medium is able to shift its perceptual focus from the corporeal plane to the ethereal plane. A medium who is viewing the ethereal plane, adopts the second degree of perception, and is, therefore, far less aware of corporeal reality (REALITY 10) The medium also acquires direct perception, and is able to communicate (and/or engage in mental conflict) with any perceived ethereal entities/components.</p>\n<p>Use of this talent does not create an astral entity. The medium&rsquo;s ethereal component remains anchored firmly to its corporeal component. The medium is, however, subject to fatigue/dissolution.</p>\n<p>This talent is subject to passive triggering. A Medium in the presence of significant ethereal phenomena may have a sense of disquiet. The more powerful the presence, the more distinct the feeling.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> include very scary nightmares, the dim perception of &ldquo;ghosts&rdquo; here and there, a dread of graveyards etc.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> sometimes has the unfortunate effect of releasing itinerant ethereals into the world. This is particularly hazardous when such entities are hostile, violent and/or in search of bodies.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 6","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, tai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"amv8Nu6TzI46vzlz"}
{"name":"Mental Bolt","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to project a blast of mental energy at any single mind within 5&times;SI yards. The victim makes an AURAL SHOCK ROLL.</p>\n<p>✟ With CS, the victim&rsquo;s Aural Shock Roll TL (Spirit EML) is reduced by twenty points.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> include devastating headaches, dizziness, etc., for the character and innocent bystanders.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> usually take the form of misdirected effects/backfires. The talent&ndash;user, or random bystander(s) suffer the full effect.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 6","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, ahnu","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1.5,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"HJOezbrxtXPDPG55"}
{"name":"Negation","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The negator enters a trance for 15&ndash;SI seconds and makes a success roll. Success creates a spherical psionic field, centred on the negator's head, whose radius is one foot times the negator's Will. The field lasts SI minutes, but may be dissolved at will by its creator. Any attempt at enchantment or psionics within, into, or out of the field, which results in CF, MF, of MS is converted to MF; CS is converted to MS and eliminates the negating field. The field requires great concentration to maintain; the negator is limited to simple activities, like walking</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> spells/talents may tend to go wrong in the character&rsquo;s presence.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> is usually fairly harmless with this talent.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 6","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, feniri","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1.5,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"M6t6yQETeHR0IvSz"}
{"name":"Prescience","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to divine the fate of a group, person, or item. Prescience is</p>\n<p>subject to passive triggering. There are two forms:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>SENSE OF DANGER An attempt to assess danger(s) in a specific location: the character enters trance for about a minute and asks, &ldquo;is this path safe?&rdquo;. MS: vague feelings of danger if there is danger within SI yards. CS: improves detail. CF: random true/false results.</li>\n<li>PRESCIENT VISION The character specifies a subject and enters trance for 12&ndash;SI hours, during which time prescient vision(s) occur. Reduce EML if the subject is hidden by magic/etc. Normally, the dreamer lacks control over the dream, but with CS, it may be possible to partly direct the enquiry. CF/MF produce visions too vague to understand. Prescience can only reveal the GM's estimate of probable events; the future may be altered.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>✟ In some cases prescience may be limited. A prescient character may only be able to predict the manner of a person&rsquo;s death, facts about a person&rsquo;s next life, romantic matters, matters of prosperity etc.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong>&nbsp;often involve a kind of passive triggering of the sense of danger. Violent dreams and/or nightmares about loved ones dying or having severe difficulties are also common.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> is usually fairly harmless with this talent.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 6","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, tai, tarael","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"5DVb5mwLDJeYCbky"}
{"name":"Psychometry","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to divine information about persons by touching an object which they have been in contact (eg. to determine a person's location from a piece of her clothing). Psychometry requires a trance for 15&ndash;SI minutes.</p>\n<p>Psychometry may also be used to divine the history/properties of the object itself, perhaps to learn the identity of the artefact&rsquo;s maker or owner(s), the age/powers of an artefact, etc. Psychometry can never be used to divine the future and works best when queries concern the present or recent past. EML should be reduced for inquiries in the distant past, or if the knowledge is magically hidden.</p>\n<p>MS usually answers any reasonable yes/no question. CS tends to provide bonus information.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> are varied &mdash; feelings of Jamais vu in connection with various objects are common.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> is usually fairly harmless with this talent.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 7","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, tai, masara","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"3fk1NmxRwDBrCOTp"}
{"name":"Pyrokinesis","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to raise the temperature of a combustible object to flash point and start a fire. The talent does not usually work on animals or people. Once the object begins to burn, the talent user has no control of the fire. The talent may be used simply to warm objects to a desired temperature less than flash point, but CF on such attempts may cause ignition. This is a &ldquo;wild&rdquo; and highly variable talent, although higher EML should improve control.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES </strong>When the character is in a condition of stress, things sometimes burst into flame in his vicinity.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> usually causes the wrong object(s) to ignite; this can be very awkward.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 7","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, angberelius, ahnu, nadai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"uQgNGsAuWSYnA9Nt"}
{"name":"Sensitivity","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>Sensitivity is subject to Passive Triggering (p. 3) and may be used actively to scan for magical/psionic effects. EML is adjusted to reflect the proximity and strength of such effect(s). The effectiveness of the talent depends on success level; CF produces random results. A sensitive character may receive Telepathy (below) without accumulating fatigue.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> are varied &mdash; &ldquo;chills&rdquo; and &ldquo;shivers&rdquo; associated with feelings of Deja vu are common.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> is usually fairly harmless with this talent.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 7","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, tarael, tai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":0.5,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"ATiijtmS5RIMEP0E"}
