{"name":"SPIRIT","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB3","description":"<p>Spirit is the personality equivalent of CONDITION. The ability to wage Mental Conflict, resist aural shock, etc.. This skill is &ldquo;semi-automatic&rdquo;; it is calculated and opened when the character is first exposed to Mental Conflict or aural shock.</p>\n<p>For Artificial Personalities, SB equals EGO. Mental conflict takes several forms. The basic resolution procedure is for each party to the conflict to test Spirit and compare results.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 7","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @wil, @wil","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":2,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"MQp53qcS9I12A1f8"}
{"name":"Telekinesis","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to move objects without touching them. The integrity of objects cannot be violated (it is not possible to move part of an object). Solids/liquids cannot be made to occupy the same volume of space. MS allows objects to be moved up to SI yards per second. CS allows instant transfer (teleportation) if desired. CF causes the object to be thrown or teleported in a random direction (possibly into another world). Objects to be moved must be within SI yards. The maximum range an object can be moved is ML &times; 10 yards.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> are varied &mdash; objects moving by themselves, getting lost, etc., are fairly common effects.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE </strong>usually involves objects moving by themselves in odd directions and at unpredictable speeds.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 7","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, nadai, ahnu","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":null,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"0aenHKCTaJMz8VW5"}
{"name":"Telepathy","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The power to transmit thoughts or emotions. With MS, messages/emotions may be received by anyone with Sensitivity talent. With CS, the messages/emotions may be received by anyone whose Aura exceeds 11. A character who receives an emotion will feel it himself &ndash; this can have an interesting effect. Transmission range is SI leagues, but clarity diminishes with range. If the sender's SI exceeds 7, the message/emotion may be directed at, received by, a specified individual.</p>\n<p>Note: Telepathy is redundant in the second and subsequent degrees of perception (since entities in such states are capable of direct perception and communication).</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> are varied &mdash; broadcast of thought or emotion, especially sharing dreams, is common.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> often involves misdirection, releasing the wrong thought/emotion, etc. Sometimes misfire has an effect similar to Metal Bolt.</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 8","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, tarael, tai, skorus","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":1.5,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"IVft9FpwyWuVG5km"}
{"name":"Transference","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to detect and employ <em>Bar&aacute;si points</em> to translate oneself from one world to another. The talent is fairly common among the older bloodlines of the Sin&aacute;i, but is quite rare among other (demi) mortals. The character does not necessarily know where the terminus of the transfer will be, but, by definition, it will generally be quite similar to the origin point.</p>\n<p>A Character using transference may bring along possessions carried within Aura inches of skin, and any living entity with which skin contact is maintained. At lower levels of mastery the talent is quite unreliable, the character may arrive missing possessions and/or companions.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES</strong> are varied &mdash; the usual kinds of headaches and dizziness &mdash; there may also be rare bouts of semi-translucence. Deja vu and Jamais vu are also very common.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> often causes the character to arrive at an unexpected destination.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 8","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, tarael, tai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":4,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"3QoP32EtjzF1gw1P"}
{"name":"Transmutation","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>The ability to change one&rsquo;s physical form (shapeshift). In nearly all cases, only one target form is available to a character with this talent. Forms are always animate entities, and hardly ever ethereal forms. Animals are most common Time to use: 1d6&times;5 minutes.</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES </strong>headaches and dizziness &mdash; there may also be rare bouts of semi- translucence.</p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong> facial disfigurement, skin discoloration, etc..</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 8","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil, tarael, tai","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":4,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"mgzwut8cOQGYy1Sx"}
{"name":"Wild Talent","type":"psionic","img":"systems/hm3/images/icons/svg/psionics.svg","data":{"notes":"OML SB1","description":"<p>A rare talent which may change into a different talent each time it is used. Each time the talent is triggered, regenerate a new talent (the same talent may repeat).</p>\n<p><strong>PSIONIC EPISODES&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>MISFIRE</strong>&nbsp;</p>","source":"HMG GM Talents 8","macros":{"type":"script","command":""},"skillBase":{"value":0,"formula":"@aur, @aur, @wil","isFormulaValid":true},"masteryLevel":0,"effectiveMasteryLevel":0,"improveFlag":false,"fatigue":null,"ritual":{"piety":0}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"J9LJZfy7UDqGwKQ1":3,"uMJCuReUWGF3X37q":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.hm3.std-psionics.mz2GoV31gOyLZUg6"}},"_id":"t1HejjO6jD8G6dwn"}
